git-reset command tips:

git reset <path> /opposite to git add <path>
--patch/-p
	interactively select chunks to reset.

git reset [<mode>] [<commit>]
  --soft
  This dose not touch index file or working tree at all(but resets the head to <commit>)

  --mixed
 Reset commit to previous changes.

  --hard
 Everything will be reset to specified commit

  --keep
Useful example:
 # git add <path>
 # some operations
 # you want to keep local changes but reset <path>
 # git reset HEAD --keep
 


